					<P><font face="Arial" size="3" color="#000086">+ 0.0 / -0.001&quot;</font></P>
				</TD>
			</TR>
		</TBODY>
	</TABLE>
</DL>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><font face="Arial" size="3"><BR>
When
specifying the dimensions of a bearing especially with a thin walled
bearing, it is usually better to specify the outside diameter and
tolerance with the wall thickness and tolerance. This reduces the
possible error caused by the stacking of tolerances that could lead
to a shaft seizure even though dimensions are all within the
specified tolerance.</font>
</P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><font face="Arial" size="3"><a href="mach_guides.htm">Machining
